00:00:02.550 --> 00:00:05.370
Connect to a Wi-Fi Network using the HTC Pure™
Welcome to AT&amp;T “How To” videos.

00:00:05.370 --> 00:00:11.020
Today we will be showing you how to connect
to a Wi-Fi network using the HTC Pure™.

00:00:11.020 --> 00:00:16.540
Important: To access the internet when connected
to Wi-Fi, the Internet Explorer browser must

00:00:16.540 --> 00:00:23.999
be used. MEdia Net, MMS and most AT&amp;T specific
applications will not be available when connected

00:00:23.999 --> 00:00:28.189
via Wi-Fi
First, we will show you how to Turn Wi-Fi

00:00:28.189 --> 00:00:30.039
on or off.
To Turn Wi-Fi On or Off, start from the today

00:00:30.039 --> 00:00:34.850
screen, tap Start.
Then, tap settings.

00:00:34.850 --> 00:00:39.809
Next, tap Connections.
Now tap Wi-Fi.

00:00:39.809 --> 00:00:46.050
Check the box next to “Turn on Wi-Fi”
to turn Wi-Fi on. Uncheck the box to turn

00:00:46.050 --> 00:00:49.272
Wi-Fi off.
Now, we will connect to a Wi-Fi Network.

00:00:49.272 --> 00:00:54.219
To connect to a Wi-Fi Network, start from
the today screen, tap Start.

00:00:54.219 --> 00:00:58.329
Then tap Settings.
Next tap Connections.

00:00:58.329 --> 00:01:02.780
Now tap Wi-Fi.
Here you will verify the “Turn on Wi-Fi”

00:01:02.780 --> 00:01:08.320
box is checked.
Then, tap Wireless Networks.

00:01:08.320 --> 00:01:14.230
To manually connect to a network, tap Add
New. NOTE: To access one of the available

00:01:14.230 --> 00:01:19.300
networks tap the desired networks and tap
Connect.

00:01:19.300 --> 00:01:25.420
Enter the network name. NOTE: If connecting
to a hidden network, check “This is a hidden

00:01:25.420 --> 00:01:29.070
network”.
Now, tap Next.

00:01:29.070 --> 00:01:35.210
Check the appropriate option and tap Next.
Then, tap Finish.

00:01:35.210 --> 00:01:38.140
The desired Wi-Fi network will be listed as
“Connected”.

00:01:38.140 --> 00:01:42.420
Finally, we will review the Wi-Fi options.
For Wi-Fi home screen, tap Menu.

00:01:42.420 --> 00:01:50.970
The following option will display.
Add New: Add a new wireless network.

00:01:50.970 --> 00:01:56.470
Remove Settings: Remove the selected Wi-Fi
network settings from the device.

00:01:56.470 --> 00:02:01.690
Edit: Edit the selected Wi-Fi network settings
from the device.

00:02:01.690 --> 00:02:05.450
Advanced:
Turn on available network notification: Check

00:02:05.450 --> 00:02:09.780
to be notified when and available Wi-Fi network
in within range.

00:02:09.780 --> 00:02:15.010
Turn off Wi-Fi is not connected in: Turns
off Wi-Fi if not connected within the set

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:16.840
timeframe.
Never

00:02:16.840 --> 00:02:18.750
30 seconds
1 minute

00:02:18.750 --> 00:02:20.640
5 minutes
10 minutes

00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:27.960
30 minutes
Turn Off Wi-Fi: Turn Wi-Fi off on the device.

00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:32.280
Press Close.
If further assistance is needed feel free

00:02:32.280 --> 00:02:40.920
to contact our online Business Support Team
at www.att.com/biztech. If accessing the site

00:02:40.920 --> 00:02:45.710
for the first time you will need to enter
your device model and click "Next".

00:02:45.710 --> 00:02:47.240
Thank you for choosing AT&amp;T.

